FBIS4-16451 "drsov074_b_94018" FBIS-SOV-94-074 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Nuclear Issues Officers' Group Seeks Cancellation of U.S. Exercises Officers' Group Seeks Cancellation of U.S. Exercises LD1804001094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 2330 GMT 17 Apr 94 LD1804001094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] The participants in the All-Union Congress of the Union of Officers held in Moscow's suburbs have decided to ask the Russian military leadership to cancel the joint Russian-American military exercises planned for the summer of this year. The Union of Officers regards assisting and participating in the maneuvers as treason. The Congress passed a resolution assessing the recent air strikes against Bosnia as preparing a bridgehead for the mounting of aggression against Russia and other Slav states. In this connection the delegates demanded an immediate convocation of the UN Security Council to end the escalation of the violence and genocide of the Serbian people. This was reported by the Interfax agency.
